<h2 id="when-to-send-emails-and-text-messages">Choosing your channel</h2>

<p>Always consider whether you can send a digital message in the NHS App first, followed by text or email. If a user doesn’t respond to a digital message, you may still be able to follow up with a letter.</p>

<p>Discuss anything you’re not sure about with your information governance team.</p>

<h2 id="transactional-messages">Messages in the NHS App</h2>

<p>Sending messages in the NHS App are a safe and secure way of communicating with patients and service users. You should:</p>

<ul>
  <li>consider the App first as it’s secure and verified</li>
  <li>keep messages short and concise</li>
  <li>put whatever matters most first</li>
  <li>use short descriptive titles</li>
  <li>include a call to action</li>
</ul>

